ndering if it’s best to avoid it. I also need to make sure to remove any deprecated APIs but still implement necessary interfaces. It seems top-level helper classes should be public, so nested static helpers in public tests make sense.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Designing test cases for datastore entities**\\n\\nI'm working on test cases for datastore entities. For the first case, I’m creating keys using `KeyFactory.createKey()` for both an account and a child order. I need to properly set properties like \\\"email\\\" and \\\"notes\\\" for the entity. I'm considering making a list for the \\\"status\\\" property as an array. For embedded entities, I’m thinking of using `setPropertiesFrom()` but might simplify it by just using `embedded.setProperty()` to keep it straightforward.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_M6mlIXN9nvNA2dW9NcvqT9cs|fc_02e483d30cfdc374016a2904e1c9d88197b6448bb553ef8110", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "grep -n \"class PropertyProjection\\|addProjection\\|setDistinct\" -n /tmp/appengine-src/com/google/appengine/api/datastore/Query.java | head -60"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1443, "output": 572, "cacheRead": 52736, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 54751, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781073100937, "responseId": "resp_02e483d30cfdc374016a2904cd83948197a81d74ac330d5c36"}}
